#axiom: do not load the universe just to draw a scrollbar

Meaning:

User interfaces should communicate progress immediately, even when full information is not yet available.

Exact scrollbars require knowing the full size of a dataset before rendering.

For large artifacts this forces the system to:
	•	scan the entire file
	•	compute layout
	•	delay feedback to the user

This is the wrong priority.

The correct priority is:

show progress first, compute precision later.

Example preferred output:

loading artifact.log
chunk 3 / ~120
≈2%

Instead of blocking the interface to compute an exact scrollbar.

Principle:

Progress before precision.

