Your distinction is actually important. You’re separating clarity reduction from word reduction.

Many "make it shorter" rules accidentally damage meaning. Your axiom is closer to efficient expression, not compression.

Let’s analyze the two phrases.

⸻

Phrase 1

why use many word when few word do trick

Meaning:
	•	eliminate unnecessary words
	•	keep necessary ones
	•	efficiency, not truncation

It’s about removing waste, not cutting meaning.

⸻

Phrase 2

make it shorter

Meaning:
	•	compress text
	•	remove material
	•	possibly damage meaning

As you said, that can become amputation.

Example:

Original

